=head1 DESCRIPTION

An error corresponding to the calculation of a route between the
C<DeparturePosition> and C<DestinationPosition>.

The error code can be one of the following:

=over

=item *

C<RouteNotFound> - Unable to find a valid route with the given
parameters.

=back

=over

=item *

C<RouteTooLong> - Route calculation went beyond the maximum size of a
route and was terminated before completion.

=back

=over

=item *

C<PositionsNotFound> - One or more of the input positions were not
found on the route network.

=back

=over

=item *

C<DestinationPositionNotFound> - The destination position was not found
on the route network.

=back

=over

=item *

C<DeparturePositionNotFound> - The departure position was not found on
the route network.

=back

=over

=item *

C<OtherValidationError> - The given inputs were not valid or a route
was not found. More information is given in the error C<Message>

=back


=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Code => Str

The type of error which occurred for the route calculation.


=head2 Message => Str

A message about the error that occurred for the route calculation.



